MARCInd1ValueLabel: Agency identified in subfield $2 or Library and Archives Canada
Justification for Mapping: $2 is not defined as a scheme, but rather the identifier for a source agency assinging the record control number
Transformation Notes:
[nomen minted for $a or $z)-->rdano:P80075-->[lookup symbol in $2 in http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/organizations , plug in IRI for organization here]
LNA 2025-02-17
Problems with Mapping:
We don't anticipate a $2 appearing in first indicator # (blank) records.  If one does, this may result in failure to map the "is assigned by corporate body" property for that field.  If a symbol assigned by LAC is in the $2, we may not be able to look it up at id.loc.gov.  We can still create an assigned by property for LAC based on indicator 1 = # (blank)
LNA 2025-02-17
